cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.DC, cs.CY, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on privacy-preserving image processing using homomorphic encryption. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also likely as the paper describes the implementation of the library as an extension to OpenCV, a popular computer vision library. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possible category as the paper discusses the delegation of image processing operations to remote servers. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possible category as the paper addresses privacy concerns related to cloud computing services. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper describes the design and implementation of the CryptoImg library.
